_:Neb8fa02aa6b243dda265c27a1e085f40 <http://schema.org/description> "<p>Catherine joined HM Courts and Tribunals Service (HMCTS) as Chief Financial Officer in June 2024.  Prior to that Catherine was Finance and Business Director for Transformation/Change in HMRC.</p>\n\n<p>This isn’t Catherine’s first role in HMCTS: she was previously responsible for Strategic Finance and Planning where she notably played a key role in our Covid-19 response and recovery efforts.  Her wider experience includes leading a £3bn delivery programme across England whilst at the Department for Work and Pensions, a number of years working at the European Commission in Brussels, and a range of policy and analytical roles in the earlier parts of her UK civil service career.</p>\n\n<p>Catherine is a chartered management accountant, holds a PhD, and is also a qualified executive coach.  Catherine is passionate about getting strategic transformation right: she believes in the strength of multi-disciplinary teams, where enabling functions are at the heart of decision-making.</p>\n" <https://forgetmenot.local/extractor/jsonld> .
